        "content": "<p>Okay, after rewriting with <code>Nat.div_self</code>, your goal is indeed <code>1 = 1</code> (as far as I can tell), but <code>rw</code> closes this goal for you. Then you have yo prove the second goal, <code>0 &lt; fact n</code></p>",
        "id": 477874000,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1729408401
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You're trying to prove with <code>exact fact_pos</code>, but <code>fact_pos</code> is a theorem that takes an explicit argument for the <code>n</code> in <code>fact n</code> (or, if you like, a function that eats an <code>n</code> and spits out a proof of <code>0 &lt; fact n</code>. So if you instead write <code>fact_pos n</code>, I think that'll solve the second goal</p>",
